{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01KrcRSnLDSP8uP448sHAgPf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Specification Validation Results\n\n### Summary: **Ready** (with one minor recommendation)\n\n---\n\n### Feedback Coverage Check\n\nAll 6 patterns from `feedback.md` are addressed:\n\n| Pattern | Feedback | Plan Fix | Status |\n|---------|----------|----------|--------|\n| A: OCR â†’ empty (2) | Braised Cod, Roasted Beet | Change 1 | Covered |\n| B: OCR â†’ body sentence (3) | Droإ¼dإ¼e Sernik, Piernik, إ»urek | Change 1 | Covered |\n| C: Partial OCR (1) | Sole with Brown Butter | Change 2 | Covered |\n| D: Erratic case â†’ body (1) | Kopytka z Pieczarkami | Change 3 | Covered |\n| E: Metadata â†’ empty (1) | Ogأ³rkowa Zupa | Change 4 | Covered |\n| F: Title absent (1) | Mushroom Risotto | Explicitly excluded (non-fixable) | Covered |\n\n---\n\n### Feasibility Within Hard Constraints\n\nAll 4 changes are O(1) per candidate, no new embedding calls, no async operations. Performance impact is negligible (<1ms). All changes are within `lib/text-classifier/`. **Fully feasible.**\n\n---\n\n### Overengineering Check\n\n- **Change 1** (preserve standalone in merge): Minimal, elegant. One extra `push()` per merged line. Not overengineered.\n- **Change 2** (add \"sole\" to dictionary): Trivial. Not overengineered.\n- **Change 3** (language-specific word-count threshold): The language branching adds modest complexity, but the linguistic justification (Polish imperatives are unambiguous, English ones aren't) is sound. Acceptable.\n- **Change 4** (raise cap 0.18 â†’ 0.22): See recommendation below.\n\n---\n\n### Cross-Iteration Contradiction Check\n\n**No significant contradictions found.** The changes build on previous iterations rather than reversing them:\n\n1. **Change 1 vs iter 16 (continuation merge):** The plan explicitly acknowledges the merge was introduced in iter 16 to fix fragmented titles. Change 1 preserves the merge behavior while also emitting the standalone â€” strictly more capable. Not a reversal.\n\n2. **Change 3 vs iter 29 (cooking instruction threshold):** Iter 29 added `ugotuj` to `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` but kept the `>= 4` word-count guard. Iter 29's unit tests show `\"Ugotuj ziemniaki w osolonej wodzie.\"` (5 words) â†’ `true`, and `\"Ugotuj\"` (1 word) â†’ `false`. But the actual failing case `\"Ugotuj ziemniaky.\"` has only 2 words, which iter 29 didn't test. Iter 30 correctly identifies this gap and proposes lowering the threshold to 2 **only for Polish**, preserving the 4-word guard for English. This is a correction of an incomplete fix, not a contradiction.\n\n3. **Change 4 vs iter 26/29 (positional cap):** Iter 26 introduced the `+0.15` cap to prevent over-boosting. Iter 29 raised it to `+0.18` for pipe+ALL_CAPS. Iter 30 proposes `+0.22`. The successive increases (0.15 â†’ 0.18 â†’ 0.22) are consistent in direction and all apply the same narrow condition (pipe-metadata + ALL_CAPS). No contradiction, but see recommendation.\n\n4. **Iter 29 fixes still active:** The plan correctly notes that iter 30 implemented all 6 iter 29 changes, and Change 1 unblocks them by preventing the continuation merge from destroying the title before those fixes can fire.\n\n---\n\n### Recommendation\n\n**Change 4 threshold bump (0.18 â†’ 0.22):** The plan's own Open Question 1 flags that the actual raw embedding score for `OGأ“RKOWA ZUPA` hasn't been verified. Three successive cap increases without empirical verification is a pattern that could lead to future regressions if the cap becomes too permissive. The plan already hedges (\"we should verify the actual raw embedding score\"), but the implementation order (Change 4 last) and the phrasing suggest it will be implemented regardless.\n\n**Suggestion:** No edit needed â€” the plan's existing Open Question 1 and the \"implement and verify\" note in the implementation order adequately address this. The Implementation Order already says \"may not be needed if Change 1 indirectly helps. Implement and verify.\" This is the right approach.\n\n---\n\n### Final Assessment\n\nThe plan is well-structured, addresses all fixable failures, stays within constraints, and avoids contradicting previous iterations. The root cause analysis (continuation merge destroying titles before OCR repair can fire) is a genuine insight that explains why iter 29's correct fixes didn't help. **Ready for implementation.**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":34337,"cache_read_input_tokens":31707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":34337},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac2d9e1b-dbea-4db9-a94b-203c0145980c","uuid":"6b70c626-72f5-4b3c-9a33-e5570ef9033c"}
